This paper uses machine learning to predict the probability of bills becoming law in the U.S. Congress. It involves natural language processing and semantic analysis, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning algorithms and models, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing data and conducting sensitivity analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
